## 📊 Key Metrics

| Metric | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| Visitors | Total website visitors |
| Page Views | Total pages viewed |
| Sessions | User visits to the website |
| Bounce Rate | Percentage of single-page visits |
| Session Duration | Average time spent on the site |
| Traffic Sources | Origin of visitors |

## 🔍 Analysis Modules

### 1. Data Cleaning & Validation
- Handle missing values
- Remove duplicate records
- Standardize data formats
- Validate dataset structure

### 2. Traffic Trend Analysis
- Daily traffic trends
- Weekly and monthly patterns
- Peak traffic identification

### 3. Traffic Source Analysis
- Organic Search
- Direct Traffic
- Social Media
- Referral Traffic
- Email Campaigns

### 4. User Engagement Analysis
- Bounce Rate Evaluation
- Session Duration Tracking
- Most Visited Pages

### 5. Visualization & Reporting
- Line Charts
- Bar Charts
- Pie Charts
- Traffic Reports

## 📈 Expected Outcomes
- Better understanding of visitor behavior
- Identification of traffic trends
- Improved website performance
- Enhanced marketing strategies
- Data-driven decision making

## ▶️ Installation

Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/Web-Traffic-Analytics.git
```

Navigate to the project directory:

```bash
cd Web-Traffic-Analytics
```

Install dependencies:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## ▶️ Usage

Run the application:

```bash
python main.py
```

